# HireAHuman — Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual values.

---

## Required

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | Your Supabase project URL | `https://abc123.supabase.co` |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Service role key for backend database access | `eyJhbG...` |

> The MCP server will refuse to start if these are missing.

---

## Core Application

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Anon/public key for client-side Supabase access | `eyJhbG...` |
| `HIREAHUMAN_API_KEY` | Master API key for CLI and development | `hak_live_your-api-key` |
| `PORT` | Port for the MCP HTTP server | `3001` |
| `API_PORT` | Port for the REST API server | `3000` |
| `WORKER_APP_URL` | Base URL of the worker app | `http://localhost:3002` |
| `ADMIN_APP_URL` | Base URL of the admin dashboard | `http://localhost:3003` |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | Comma-separated allowed origins | `http://localhost:3001,http://localhost:3002` |

---

## Database & Cache

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Direct PostgreSQL connection string (for migrations) | `postgresql://postgres:password@db.supabase.co:5432/postgres` |
| `REDIS_URL` | Redis connection string (rate limiting & caching) | `redis://localhost:6379` |

---

## Payments (Stripe)

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `PAYMENT_PROVIDER` | Payment provider (currently only `stripe`) | `stripe` |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Stripe secret key | `sk_live_...` |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | Stripe webhook endpoint secret | `whsec_...` |
| `STRIPE_ACCOUNT_ID` | Stripe connected account ID (if using Connect) | `acct_...` |

---

## Notifications

### Email (Nodemailer / SMTP)

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `NOTIFY_EMAIL_HOST` | SMTP server hostname | `smtp.gmail.com` |
| `NOTIFY_EMAIL_PORT` | SMTP server port | `587` |
| `NOTIFY_EMAIL_USER` | SMTP username / email address | `notifications@hireahuman.ai` |
| `NOTIFY_EMAIL_PASS` | SMTP password or app-specific password | `xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx` |
| `NOTIFY_EMAIL_FROM` | Default From address | `HireAHuman <notifications@hireahuman.ai>` |

### Slack

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `NOTIFY_SLACK_WEBHOOK` | Slack Incoming Webhook URL | `https://hooks.slack.com/services/...` |

### Telegram

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `NOTIFY_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | Telegram Bot API token | `123456:ABC-DEF1234...` |

### SMS (Twilio)

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `NOTIFY_SMS_PROVIDER` | SMS provider (currently only `twilio`) | `twilio` |
| `NOTIFY_SMS_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio Account SID | `ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx` |
| `NOTIFY_SMS_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio Auth Token | `xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx` |
| `NOTIFY_SMS_FROM` | Twilio phone number to send from | `+15551234567` |

---

## Optional / Advanced

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `DEFAULT_TENANT_ID` | Fallback tenant ID for stdio MCP mode | `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000` |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | Server log level | `info` |
| `NODE_ENV` | Runtime environment | `development` |
